  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: 2.28.0\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\nI use Erigon for Binance Smart Chain.\r\nWhen I try to get the transaction receipt request fails with an error. Other transactions in the same block work fine. \r\n```\r\ncurl <url> \\\r\n-X POST \\\r\n-H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\r\n-d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getTransactionReceipt\",\"params\":[\"0x2d84efb3d39b8209813d6d217d98530dd1d2188e9005399d7203a1f628b199cc\"],\"id\":0}'\r\n```\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nShould return proper transaction receipt\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n```\r\nEROR[11-04|15:05:08.481] RPC method eth_getTransactionReceipt crashed: runtime error: slice bounds out of range [19:5]\r\n[service.go:217 panic.go:838 panic.go:117 decompress.go:541 block_reader.go:686 block_reader.go:787 block_snapshots.go:312 block_reader.go:786 eth_api.go:141 eth_receipts.go:453 value.go:556 value.go:339 service.go:222 handler.go:494 handler.go:444 handler.go:392 handler.go:186 asm_amd64.s:1571]\r\n```\r\n",
